the political charge of precarious dwelling. It is there, if often in unannounced ways, that a profound struggle for a differential kind of homing signals multiple possibilities to transcend the violences of home/homelessness. In advancing a new approach to work with the politics of inhabitation, Lancione provides a critique of current practices and offers a transformative vision for a renewed, liberatory politics of home.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aHomexPolitical aspects. 0aHome-Political aspects. 0aHomeless persons. 0aHomelessnessxPolitical aspects. 0aHomelessness-Political aspects. 0aHuman geography. 0aMarginality, Social. 0aSociology, Urban. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Urban.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478027423?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478027423423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478027423/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131926-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSLb2023